Setting up G
-install the go distribution for your OS

-create a Go/GO/go dir under ~, this is GO_HOME, create that env
-under GO_HOME, add src, pkg and bin

-add GO_HOME/bin to $PATH
-add GOPATH as $HOME/Go
-add GOBIN as $GO_HOME/bin

-add /usr/local/go/bin to your $PATH


Install Go Tools
-install the go get and gofmt 



Go Get
------
to get a go repo from git (ex: https://github.com/goinaction/code.git)
 > go get github.com/goinaction/code.git

 will download and install into your GOPATH/src directory